page.title: 19Home Life.
page.content: My Saturday. I have Coco Pops for breakfast,then brush my teeth with Crest toothpaste. I go outside to play on the swing. I like to go high, as high as the fence. I go inside to watch 'Number 73' on T.V.then we go shopping to Leyburn. We have fish and chips for lunch which we eat in the car. I just have chips. If I can't eat them all I give them to the pigeons.I have 50p. pocket money. I spend it on key rings & pencil sharpeners.When I get home I play with Rebecca. She lives on a farm & has 4 dogs. We paddle in the Beck when it is hot.For tea I have salad sandwiches,then ride my bike up High Fields. At bedtime I put on my night_ dress and read my book,'Milly Molly Mandy'. At 9.30pm. I watch 'Tales Of The Unexpected' on my T.V.in my bedroom then go to sleep.
